RPi-EEPROM-AT24C256

Read and write data to an AT24C256-based EEPROM integrated circuit over the
i2c bus on a Raspberry Pi. The AT24C256 stores 32768 bytes (256Kbit), so
memory addresses 0-32767 are available.

This is an XS distribution: it compiles a small C layer that drives the
kernel's /dev/i2c-N SMBus interface, so it builds and runs on Linux (the
Raspberry Pi) only.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc RPi::EEPROM::AT24C256

You can also look for information at:

    Github (report bugs here)
        https://github.com/stevieb9/rpi-eeprom-at24c256/issues

    Search MetaCPAN
        https://metacpan.org/dist/RPi-EEPROM-AT24C256


